{
  "texts": [
    "introduced Self-Paced Learning (SPL) [50] as an extension of curriculum learning (CL), which Bengio proposed in 2009 [51].",
    "SPL is based on the idea of mimicking how humans learn: starting with simple examples and gradually moving to more complex ones [52].",
    "Specifically, SPL addresses dataset issues such as class imbalance and corrupted labels by adding a pace-controlled regularization term to the learning objective.",
    "A minimal form is:min θ, w∈[0,1] n n i=1 w i L(y i, ŷi) + r(w i, c),(1)where ŷi denotes the model prediction for x i, L is any supervised loss, and r(•; c) is the self-paced regularizer with pace c > 0.",
    "Here, w i ∈ [0, 1] is the self-paced weight assigned to sample i and is optimized jointly with θ."
  ]
}